result.execSummary:
The defendant Dale Robert Nagel was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Operate with Restricted Controlled Substance (4th w/in 5 yrs), a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(1)(am).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Dale Robert Nagel in court with attorney Joseph Smith.  David John Behm appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count 1.  Court finds defendant guilty.  Count #2 is dismissed and read in.   The Defendant was sentenced to the following:

IMPOSED AND STAYED SENTENCE OF:   

6 YEARS IMPRISONMENT.
3 YEARS OF INITIAL CONFINEMENT.
3 YEARS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION.

*D/L REVOCATION: 36 months.
*IGNITION INTERLOCK: 36 months.

TERM OF PROBATION:  3 YEAR(S);

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:  
*AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
*Absolute Sobriety;  Random U.A.'s ; 
*No Use or Possession of alcohol, controlled substances or drug paraphernalia
*No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
*Any valid prescription drugs must be taken only in the manner in which they are prescribed.
*Inform Agent of all prescriptions
*Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
*Maintain full time employment and/or combination of schooling 
*DNA sample to be provided if not yet previously done.
*Attend Victim Impact Panel. 
*Perform 50 hours of community service per year for a total of 150 hours of community service. 

BLOOD DRAW FEE:  $35.00 (to be paid as a condition of probation - to be forward to the City of Muskego Police Department);

FINE:  $1469.00 (apply cash bail, balance to be paid as a condition of probation);

DNA SURCHARGE: $250.00

CONDITION TIME:  12 MONTHS, FIRST 2 months to be served as Straight time, last 10 months to be served  as NON WORKING HOURS w/Standard Release Conditions. (apply 1 day credit) to begin forthwith.

DAY REPORT CENTER:  1 year Day Report Center (consecutive to Condition time).

Felony warnings, voting rights and firearms warnings given.
